Amcon Writes Off $1.9 Billion Oceanic Loans, ThisDay Reports

-- B y   E m e l e   O n u
-- 
2011-09-11T09:30:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-11/amcon-writes-off-1-9-billion-oceanic-loans-thisday-reports.html
State-run Asset Management Corp. of
 Nigeria  has written off 290 billion naira ($1.9 billion) of non-
performing loans to  Oceanic Bank International Plc (OCEANIC)  so that a
proposed takeover of the bank can go ahead, ThisDay  reported .  The move would enable acquirer Ecobank Transnational to
recapitalize Oceanic to the required level of capital adequacy,
the newspaper said, without identifying a source.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emele Onu in Johannesburg at 
 eonu1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  